title: Help I just dropped a straw in my gas tank! : r/Advice - Reddit
body: MengerianMango Advice Guru [92] • 7 yr. ago. There's not much you can do. You'd have to take the gas tank off to get it out. The straw alone shouldn't be enough to plug the fuel pump, but, if it dissolves, then it might plug the fuel pump filter. If it does, then you're going to have to have that replaced, which also requires removing the tank.
